HEADWORD: dinoflagellate
<hw>dinoflagellate</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a member of the
<ord>Dinoflagellata</ord>, chiefly marine protozoa having two flagella.
The dinoflagellates form a chief constituent of plankton.</def>⟦br⟧
